        Frequently Asked <span class="text-accent">Questions</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8" open>
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is a hinged steel belt conveyor?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>A hinged steel belt conveyor uses interlocking steel plates connected by hinge pins to form a rugged continuous belt. The overlapping plates handle hot chips, sharp scrap, and heavy metalworking debris that would destroy rubber or plastic belts. It is the standard chip removal system for CNC machines and stamping presses.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What can a hinged steel belt conveyor handle?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Metal chips, turnings, stamping scrap, die-cast parts, hot forgings, and heavy industrial waste. Handles temperatures up to 900&deg;F, sharp edges, coolant exposure, and impact loading. Load capacity from light chip duty to over 1,000 lbs per linear foot for heavy stamping scrap.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            How does a hinged steel belt differ from wire mesh?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Hinged steel belts use solid overlapping plates (closed surface) for heavy scrap and chip handling. <a href="/conveyor-types/wire-mesh-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Wire mesh belts</a> use open-weave wire for airflow and drainage in ovens, freezers, and wash systems. Hinged steel handles heavier loads and sharper materials. Wire mesh handles heat transfer and drainage applications.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What maintenance does a hinged steel belt require?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Daily chip jam removal and drainage checks. Weekly hinge pin and plate inspection. Monthly chain tension and motor amperage checks. Individual damaged plates can be field-replaced without removing the entire belt. Typical belt life is 5-15 years depending on application severity.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-ink-light" aria-labelledby="related-heading">
